-- Shin-Etsu Chemical to Build Silicone Factory in China By 2012, Nikkei Says
-- Chris Cooper
-- 2010-06-27T00:20:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/shin-etsu-chemical-to-build-silicone-factory-in-china-by-2012-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Shin-Etsu Chemical Co. will build a
silicone factory in China by 2012, the Nikkei newspaper said,
without saying where it got the information.  
 The factory will provide silicone for use in cars and
consumer electronics and have an annual capacity of 25,000
metric tons, the report said.  
